{"build_type":"library","description":"Advance function for the ordered collector fiber kind (category 6): a worker whose cycle delivers the children it launches in LAUNCH order, streaming via a reorder buffer rather than waiting for all. On first entry it allocates a reorder buffer (cursor, accumulator, per-index filled flags and result slots), seeds remaining = 3, stores the buffer pointer in its own slot 7, and fans out three category-7 ordered children carrying inputs 1,2,3 and launch indices 0,1,2, then parks at pc 1. The completion routing re-readies it on each child completion; each resumed pass drains the contiguous filled prefix of the buffer in launch order (folding acc = acc*10 + result), decrements remaining, and parks again. When the last child completes the fully drained accumulator is the launch-order delivery, placed in the result slot and routed to its own awaiter. Streaming ordered delivery, purely cooperative, no eventfd, no clone.","module_name":"advance-ordered-collector-fiber-within-cooperative-scheduler","package_name":"advance-ordered-collector-fiber-within-cooperative-scheduler","function_definitions":{"advance-ordered-collector-fiber-within-cooperative-scheduler":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"s","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"t","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"two","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":2},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"three","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":3},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"four","v